      "page": 31,
      "context": "1. Check carburetor heat control for proper rigging. If partially open it would cause a slight power loss. 2. Check magneto timing, spark plugs and igni- tion harness for settings and conditions. 3. Check condition of induction air filter. Clean if necessary. 4. Perform an engine compression check. (Re- fer to engine Manufacturer's Manual)."
    },
    {
      "source": "1975_cessna_172_skyhawk_aviation/.splits_Cessna 172 & Skyhawk Series Service Manual (1969 - 1976)/Cessna 172 & Skyhawk Series Service Manual (1969 - 1976)_part04_p151-200.pdf",
