  "diagnostic_reasoning": "The reported RPM drop exceeding 125 RPM on one magneto, accompanied by rough engine operation, indicates an issue within the ignition system specific to that magneto. The Service Manual states that an RPM drop exceeding 125 RPM or a differential greater than 50 RPM between magnetos is outside normal limits (Source 1, page 21). A 'sharp rpm drop-off past normal is usually a sign of a fouled plug, a defective harness lead or a magneto out of time' (Source 6, page 21). The FSM also directs that 'If ignition trouble should develop, spark plugs and ignition wiring should be checked first' (Source 15, page 20). Other potential causes for power loss, such as carburetor heat or induction filter, are less likely to manifest as a problem isolated to a single magneto's performance during a run-up.",
  "mechanic_instructions": "The excessive RPM drop and rough running on one magneto during run-up points directly to a fault in that magneto's ignition circuit. Per the Service Manual, we need to start by inspecting the most common failure points. Begin by checking the spark plugs and ignition harness for the cylinders associated with the affected magneto.",
  "answer_path_prompts": [
    "The spark plugs for the affected magneto's cylinders are fouled, worn, or improperly gapped. (Refer to paragraph 11-60 for spark plug maintenance, Source 6, page 21; and 11-9 for troubleshooting, Source 45, page 4).",
    "The ignition harness leads for the affected magneto show signs of damage, chafing, or a lack of continuity. (Refer to paragraph 11-9 for troubleshooting, Source 45, page 4).",
    "The magneto-to-engine timing for the affected magneto is outside the specified tolerance of plus zero, minus two degrees. (Refer to paragraph 11-58 for timing checks, Source 27, page 20; and 11A-18A for static run-up checks, Source 10, page 31).",
    "The magneto itself is defective, showing signs of internal moisture or other malfunction not attributable to plugs, harness, or timing. (Refer to paragraph 11-58 for troubleshooting, Source 15, page 20)."
  ],
  "requires_input": true
}

